Package: sgeasy
Title: Downstream Analysis for Saturation Genome Editing Screens
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jamie", "Billington", email = "jb63@sanger.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Andrew", "Waters", email = "aw29@sanger.ac.uk",
           role = "aut")
    )
Description: Provides a user-friendly workflow for analyzing saturation genome
    editing (SGE) screen data. Includes functions for data normalization
    using control oligos, DESeq2-based differential abundance analysis,
    and visualization utilities for quality control and results
    exploration. Designed to work with QUANTS output and VEP annotations.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/team113sanger/sgeasy
